[[File:Peoria, Illinois, city directory (1910) (14577395708).jpg|alt=A list of persons by house number, on a street|thumb|1910 directory page for North Adams Street, [[Peoria, Illinois]]]]

A '''city directory''' is a listing of residents, streets,  businesses, organizations or institutions, giving their location in a [[city]].  It may be arranged alphabetically or geographically or in other ways.  Antedating [[telephone directories]], they were in use for centuries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.oberlinheritagecenter.org/researchlearn/directories|title=City Directories|website=www.oberlinheritagecenter.org|language=en|access-date=2017-05-22}}</ref>  Many older directories have been digitized and are available on the open web and through subscription databases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://guides.nyu.edu/c.php?g=276753&p=1845804|title=Research Guides: New York City: City Directories|last=Moazeni|first=Sarah|website=guides.nyu.edu|language=en|access-date=2017-05-22}}</ref>

Examples included [[Kelly's Directory]] and the [[Boston Directory]].

